TY  - JOUR
T1  - Staffing Policy as a Strategic Response: A Typology of Career Systems
AU  - Sonnenfeld, Jeffrey A.
AU  - Peiperl, Maury A.
Y1  - 1988/10/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1988.4307437
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1988.4307437
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 588
EP  - 600
VL  - 13
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This article proposes a four-cell typology of career systems, reflecting two critical dimensions along which firms choose a staffing strategy, supply flow and assignment flow. We suggest that this typology reflects, in a human resources context, the different choices firms make in managing their overall strategy. The career systems profiles that follow from the typology both describe and predict the composition of a company's work force.
AB  - This article proposes a four-cell typology of career systems, reflecting two critical dimensions along which firms choose a staffing strategy, supply flow and assignment flow. We suggest that this typology reflects, in a human resources context, the different choices firms make in managing their overall strategy. The career systems profiles that follow from the typology both describe and predict the composition of a company's work force.
