T1  - Forms of Value Systems: Focus on Organizational Effectiveness and Cultural Change and Maintenance
AU  - Wiener, Yoash
Y1  - 1988/10/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.1988.4307410
DO  - 10.5465/amr.1988.4307410
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 534
EP  - 545
VL  - 13
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The study of organizational culture may benefit from a focus on shared values, one of its measurable core elements. A typology of value systems based on the content (functional-elitist) and source (traditional-charismatic leadership) of values permits a contingency approach for the analysis of the emergence, change, and maintenance of a culture as well as the contributions culture makes to organizational effectiveness.
AB  - The study of organizational culture may benefit from a focus on shared values, one of its measurable core elements. A typology of value systems based on the content (functional-elitist) and source (traditional-charismatic leadership) of values permits a contingency approach for the analysis of the emergence, change, and maintenance of a culture as well as the contributions culture makes to organizational effectiveness.
